A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a greenhouse made of glass panels and metal framework, but instead of plants growing inside, abstract geometric user interface elements emerge organically from the soil—rounded rectangles, navigation bars, and tab-like shapes sprouting upward like seedlings reaching toward filtered sunlight. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones typical of mid-century modern design. Soft watercolor textures blend with clean architectural lines. Morning light streams through the glass roof, casting long geometric shadows across the interior. The composition suggests growth, evolution, and careful cultivation of digital design systems within a nurturing environment.
